  "content": "The title of the 1994 publication is: **Chemical modification of surfactin: influence of ester chain length on surface-active properties**\n\nPublished in *Biotechnology and Applied Biochemistry*, this study detailed the chemical modification of surfactin through the targeted addition of simple alkyl ester moieties. The research involved contributions from teams at Claude Bernard University Lyon 1 and experts from ICSN (Institut des Composés Bioactifs et des Nutriments Végétaux), the French national center focused on natural substances chemistry. The investigation characterized how ester chain length modifications impacted surface activity, cell-lysing potential, and affinity for divalent cations.",
